about.summary: Jupyter bundler extension to export notebook as a docx file

name: jupyter-docx-bundler
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyter-docx-bundler" %}
{% set version = "0.2.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9457377f8d25dcde1a4de241f31ddc31d18d503f00ccf02823393729196584a1

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [py<36]
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools >=38.6.0
    - setuptools_scm
  run:
    - python
    - notebook >=5.0
    - pypandoc >=1.4
    - nbconvert >=5.5
    - pandoc >=2.0
    - requests
    - tornado

test:
  imports:
    - jupyter_docx_bundler

about:
  home: https://github.com/m-rossi/jupyter-docx-bundler
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Jupyter bundler extension to export notebook as a docx file'
  dev_url: https://github.com/m-rossi/jupyter-docx-bundler

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - m-rossi
